<subSubSection id="FBF16577FFFFFFC4FF7D2938F52FFD85" pageId="8" pageNumber="297" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="B35436FCFFFFFFC4FF7D2938F3E9F7CE" blockId="8.[151,760,1574,2078]" pageId="8" pageNumber="297">
<emphasis id="819FEAEEFFFFFFC4FF7D2938F01DF9EE" bold="true" box="[151,268,1574,1598]" pageId="8" pageNumber="297">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Antennae brown. Antennomere II longer than III. Smoky stripe on pronotum not reaching posterior margin of pronotum. Thoracic and abdominal pleurites and sternites with black spots (
<figureCitation id="2BD02A79FFFFFFC4FE352999F320F94E" box="[479,561,1671,1694]" captionStart="Figs 1" captionStartId="2.[151,188,2036,2055]" captionTargetBox="[239,1341,201,1954]" captionTargetId="figure-13@2.[179,1408,189,1996]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Figs 1A–F. Dorsal and ventral surface. A–B – Hypoxys amyoti sp. nov.; C–D – Hypoxys aspilogaster sp. nov.; E–F – Hypoxys belenensis sp. nov. Scale bars = 5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5177529" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5177529/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="297">Fig. 1B</figureCitation>
). Anterior excavation of metasternal process harboring fourth and almost whole third rostral segment (
<figureCitation id="2BD02A79FFFFFFC4FE3429D9F324F90E" box="[478,565,1735,1758]" captionStart="Figs 6" captionStartId="9.[150,187,2010,2029]" captionTargetBox="[188,1400,201,1947]" captionTargetId="figure-16@9.[187,1401,189,1973]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Figs 6A–F.Hypoxys amyoti sp. nov.A–D – pygophore in dorsal, ventral, posterior and posterolateral view, respectively; E – genital plates; F – metasternal process. Abbteviations: dr – dorsal rim; gp – superior process of the genital cup; lat 8 – laterotergites 8; lat 9 – laterotergites 9; pa – parameres; proc – proctiger; vf 8 – valvifers 8; vf 9 – valvifers 9; vr – ventral rim; vre – ventral rim expansions; x – tenth segment. Scale bars = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5177539" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5177539/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="297">Fig. 6F</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis id="819FEAEEFFFFFFC4FDA129D8F3E6F90E" bold="true" box="[587,759,1734,1758]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="297">Male genitalia.</emphasis>
Pygophore (
<figureCitation id="2BD02A79FFFFFFC4FEFD29F9F080F92E" box="[279,401,1767,1790]" captionStart="Figs 6" captionStartId="9.[150,187,2010,2029]" captionTargetBox="[188,1400,201,1947]" captionTargetId="figure-16@9.[187,1401,189,1973]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Figs 6A–F.Hypoxys amyoti sp. nov.A–D – pygophore in dorsal, ventral, posterior and posterolateral view, respectively; E – genital plates; F – metasternal process. Abbteviations: dr – dorsal rim; gp – superior process of the genital cup; lat 8 – laterotergites 8; lat 9 – laterotergites 9; pa – parameres; proc – proctiger; vf 8 – valvifers 8; vf 9 – valvifers 9; vr – ventral rim; vre – ventral rim expansions; x – tenth segment. Scale bars = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5177539" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5177539/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="297">Figs 6A–D</figureCitation>
). Posterolateral angles developed, bent inwards, acuminate (
<figureCitation id="2BD02A79FFFFFFC4FE592819F31DF8CE" box="[435,524,1799,1822]" captionStart="Figs 6" captionStartId="9.[150,187,2010,2029]" captionTargetBox="[188,1400,201,1947]" captionTargetId="figure-16@9.[187,1401,189,1973]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Figs 6A–F.Hypoxys amyoti sp. nov.A–D – pygophore in dorsal, ventral, posterior and posterolateral view, respectively; E – genital plates; F – metasternal process. Abbteviations: dr – dorsal rim; gp – superior process of the genital cup; lat 8 – laterotergites 8; lat 9 – laterotergites 9; pa – parameres; proc – proctiger; vf 8 – valvifers 8; vf 9 – valvifers 9; vr – ventral rim; vre – ventral rim expansions; x – tenth segment. Scale bars = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5177539" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5177539/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="297">Fig. 6A</figureCitation>
). Superior process of genital cup trilobate, curved, elongated, parallel to dorsal rim and almost reaching apex of posterolateral angle; inner part bifid, forming two small lobes; outer part tapering (
<figureCitation id="2BD02A79FFFFFFC4FF002899F069F84E" box="[234,376,1927,1950]" captionStart="Figs 6" captionStartId="9.[150,187,2010,2029]" captionTargetBox="[188,1400,201,1947]" captionTargetId="figure-16@9.[187,1401,189,1973]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Figs 6A–F.Hypoxys amyoti sp. nov.A–D – pygophore in dorsal, ventral, posterior and posterolateral view, respectively; E – genital plates; F – metasternal process. Abbteviations: dr – dorsal rim; gp – superior process of the genital cup; lat 8 – laterotergites 8; lat 9 – laterotergites 9; pa – parameres; proc – proctiger; vf 8 – valvifers 8; vf 9 – valvifers 9; vr – ventral rim; vre – ventral rim expansions; x – tenth segment. Scale bars = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5177539" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5177539/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="297">Figs 6A,C,D</figureCitation>
). Paramere with two lobes; anterior lobe square, curved upwards; lateral lobe rounded (
<figureCitation id="2BD02A79FFFFFFC4FD2228B9F1C4F80E" captionStart="Figs 6" captionStartId="9.[150,187,2010,2029]" captionTargetBox="[188,1400,201,1947]" captionTargetId="figure-16@9.[187,1401,189,1973]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Figs 6A–F.Hypoxys amyoti sp. nov.A–D – pygophore in dorsal, ventral, posterior and posterolateral view, respectively; E – genital plates; F – metasternal process. Abbteviations: dr – dorsal rim; gp – superior process of the genital cup; lat 8 – laterotergites 8; lat 9 – laterotergites 9; pa – parameres; proc – proctiger; vf 8 – valvifers 8; vf 9 – valvifers 9; vr – ventral rim; vre – ventral rim expansions; x – tenth segment. Scale bars = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5177539" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5177539/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="297">Figs 6C,D</figureCitation>
). Proctiger with dense crown of setae; posterior face subpentagonal and short (
<figureCitation id="2BD02A79FFFFFFC4FE3128F9F35CF82E" box="[475,589,2023,2046]" captionStart="Figs 6" captionStartId="9.[150,187,2010,2029]" captionTargetBox="[188,1400,201,1947]" captionTargetId="figure-16@9.[187,1401,189,1973]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Figs 6A–F.Hypoxys amyoti sp. nov.A–D – pygophore in dorsal, ventral, posterior and posterolateral view, respectively; E – genital plates; F – metasternal process. Abbteviations: dr – dorsal rim; gp – superior process of the genital cup; lat 8 – laterotergites 8; lat 9 – laterotergites 9; pa – parameres; proc – proctiger; vf 8 – valvifers 8; vf 9 – valvifers 9; vr – ventral rim; vre – ventral rim expansions; x – tenth segment. Scale bars = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5177539" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5177539/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="297">Figs 6C,D</figureCitation>
). Expansions of ventral rim acuminate, broadly excavated ventrolaterally,
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="B35436FCFFFFFFC4FCD62FA0F48DFF05" blockId="8.[828,1437,191,1237]" box="[828,1436,190,213]" pageId="8" pageNumber="297">with brown spot dorsally; barely surpassing level of pos-</paragraph>
<paragraph id="B35436FCFFFFFFC4FCD62FC0F52FFD85" blockId="8.[828,1437,191,1237]" pageId="8" pageNumber="297">
terolateral angles (
<figureCitation id="2BD02A79FFFFFFC4FBEB2FC0F565FF25" box="[1025,1140,222,245]" captionStart="Figs 6" captionStartId="9.[150,187,2010,2029]" captionTargetBox="[188,1400,201,1947]" captionTargetId="figure-16@9.[187,1401,189,1973]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Figs 6A–F.Hypoxys amyoti sp. nov.A–D – pygophore in dorsal, ventral, posterior and posterolateral view, respectively; E – genital plates; F – metasternal process. Abbteviations: dr – dorsal rim; gp – superior process of the genital cup; lat 8 – laterotergites 8; lat 9 – laterotergites 9; pa – parameres; proc – proctiger; vf 8 – valvifers 8; vf 9 – valvifers 9; vr – ventral rim; vre – ventral rim expansions; x – tenth segment. Scale bars = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5177539" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5177539/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="297">Figs 6A,B</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis id="819FEAEEFFFFFFC4FB6C2FC3F456FF25" bold="true" box="[1158,1351,221,245]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="297">Female genitalia.</emphasis>
Genital plates (
<figureCitation id="2BD02A79FFFFFFC4FC632FE0F2CDFEC5" box="[905,988,254,277]" captionStart="Figs 6" captionStartId="9.[150,187,2010,2029]" captionTargetBox="[188,1400,201,1947]" captionTargetId="figure-16@9.[187,1401,189,1973]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Figs 6A–F.Hypoxys amyoti sp. nov.A–D – pygophore in dorsal, ventral, posterior and posterolateral view, respectively; E – genital plates; F – metasternal process. Abbteviations: dr – dorsal rim; gp – superior process of the genital cup; lat 8 – laterotergites 8; lat 9 – laterotergites 9; pa – parameres; proc – proctiger; vf 8 – valvifers 8; vf 9 – valvifers 9; vr – ventral rim; vre – ventral rim expansions; x – tenth segment. Scale bars = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5177539" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5177539/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="297">Fig. 6E</figureCitation>
). Posterior margin of each valvifer 8 with dentiform posterolateral angles, directed posteriorly; inner angles dentiform, reaching valvifers 9; imaginary line tangent to posterolateral angles reaching distal margin of valvifers 9; inner margin slightly projected posteriorly, leaving bottom of excavation convex; excavation U-shaped. Valvulae 8 barely visible. Apices of laterotergites 8 clearly above level of apices of abdominal segment VII. Laterotergites 9 surpassing band connecting laterotergites 8; apices just passing imaginary line tangent to apices of abdominal segment VII.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="FBF16577FFFFFFC4FCB02D40F55AFCC5" pageId="8" pageNumber="297" type="description">
<paragraph id="B35436FCFFFFFFC4FCB02D40F55AFCC5" blockId="8.[828,1437,191,1237]" pageId="8" pageNumber="297">
<emphasis id="819FEAEEFFFFFFC4FCB02D40F2EAFDA5" bold="true" box="[858,1019,606,629]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="297">Measurements</emphasis>
(n = 3; mm). Total length 15.9–16.3; head length 1.6–2.0; head width 3.4–3.5; pronotum width 10.0–10.2; abdomen width 8.1–8.2; length of antennomeres: I – 0.6–0.9; II – 1.6–1.7; III – 0.9–1.1; IV – 3.5–3.7; V – 3.9; scutellum length 6.8–7.2; scutellum width 5.6–5.8; pronotum length 3.3–3.6.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="FBF16577FFFFFFC4FCD62C03F41AFBE5" pageId="8" pageNumber="297" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="B35436FCFFFFFFC4FCD62C03F41AFBE5" blockId="8.[828,1437,191,1237]" pageId="8" pageNumber="297">
<emphasis id="819FEAEEFFFFFFC4FCD62C03F537FCE5" bold="true" box="[828,1062,797,821]" pageId="8" pageNumber="297">Differential diagnosis.</emphasis>
This species resembles 
<taxonomicName id="74EB4D7FFFFFFFC4FAFE2C00F248FC85" authority="Mendonca &amp; Nunes &amp; Fernandes, 2021" authorityName="Mendonca &amp; Nunes &amp; Fernandes" authorityYear="2021" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Hypoxys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="297" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aspilogaster" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="819FEAEEFFFFFFC4FAFE2C00F248FC85" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="297">H. aspilogaster</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="9AAC5795FFFFFFC4FCB42C20F2BFFC85" box="[862,942,830,853]" pageId="8" pageNumber="297" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
and 
<taxonomicName id="74EB4D7FFFFFFFC4FC342C20F53AFC85" authority="Mendonca &amp; Nunes &amp; Fernandes, 2021" authorityName="Mendonca &amp; Nunes &amp; Fernandes" authorityYear="2021" box="[990,1067,830,853]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Hypoxys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="297" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="stysi" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="819FEAEEFFFFFFC4FC342C20F53AFC85" box="[990,1067,830,853]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="297">H. stysi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="9AAC5795FFFFFFC4FBDA2C20F591FC85" box="[1072,1152,830,853]" pageId="8" pageNumber="297" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
in the shape of the trilobate superior process of genital cup, but the shape of the paramere and the posterior face of the proctiger separate them. The female genitalia of 
<taxonomicName id="74EB4D7FFFFFFFC4FBEC2C80F57CFC65" authority="Mendonca &amp; Nunes &amp; Fernandes, 2021" authorityName="Mendonca &amp; Nunes &amp; Fernandes" authorityYear="2021" box="[1030,1133,926,949]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Hypoxys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="297" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="amyoti" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="819FEAEEFFFFFFC4FBEC2C80F57CFC65" box="[1030,1133,926,949]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="297">H. amyoti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="9AAC5795FFFFFFC4FB9E2C80F5D4FC65" box="[1140,1221,926,949]" pageId="8" pageNumber="297" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
and 
<taxonomicName id="74EB4D7FFFFFFFC4FB1D2C80F454FC65" authority="Mendonca &amp; Nunes &amp; Fernandes, 2021" authorityName="Mendonca &amp; Nunes &amp; Fernandes" authorityYear="2021" box="[1271,1349,926,949]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Hypoxys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="297" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="stysi" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="819FEAEEFFFFFFC4FB1D2C80F454FC65" box="[1271,1349,926,949]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="297">H. stysi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="9AAC5795FFFFFFC4FAA62C80F48CFC65" box="[1356,1437,926,949]" pageId="8" pageNumber="297" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
are very similar showing the bottom of the excavation of valvifers 8 convex. Both species can be hardly separated using only females; the length of laterotergite 9 seems to be the only character with visible difference.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="FBF16577FFFFFFC4FCD62B20F281FB05" pageId="8" pageNumber="297" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="B35436FCFFFFFFC4FCD62B20F281FB05" blockId="8.[828,1437,191,1237]" pageId="8" pageNumber="297">
<emphasis id="819FEAEEFFFFFFC4FCD62B20F2ACFB86" bold="true" box="[828,957,1086,1110]" pageId="8" pageNumber="297">Etymology.</emphasis>
Named after Charles Jean-Baptiste Amyot (1799–1866), the great French entomologist and one of the first researchers dedicated to the study of Heteroptera. 
<emphasis id="819FEAEEFFFFFFC4FCD62B83F2DAFB65" bold="true" box="[828,971,1181,1205]" pageId="8" pageNumber="297">Distribution</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="2BD02A79FFFFFFC4FC342B80F559FB65" box="[990,1096,1182,1205]" captionStart="Figs 21" captionStartId="27.[151,188,2061,2080]" captionTargetBox="[168,1422,190,2036]" captionTargetId="figure-16@27.[165,1422,189,2037]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="Figs 21A–B. Occurrence maps of the sixteen new species of the Hypoxys balteatus species group." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5177567" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5177567/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="297">Fig. 21A</figureCitation>
). 
<collectingCountry id="CBFC766CFFFFFFC4FBB52B80F5DDFB65" box="[1119,1228,1182,1205]" name="Suriname" pageId="8" pageNumber="297">Suriname</collectingCountry>
: Powakka; 
<collectingCountry id="CBFC766CFFFFFFC4FABA2B80F29DFB05" name="French Guiana" pageId="8" pageNumber="297">French Guiana</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
